LAYER 3: OBJECT CORRESPONDENCE
how Fadriel sees that objects in input MAP to objects in output

observe spatial_perception.rana

many puzzles establish a MAPPING between input objects and output objects:
"this red dot in the input corresponds to this red region in the output"
the correspondence can be by color, position, shape, or order

@spatial_rule one_to_one_mapping
DETECT same number of foreground clusters in input and output
MATCH each input cluster to the output cluster with same color
LEARN the transform for each matched pair (moved? resized? recolored? stamped?)
VERIFY all matches undergo same transform type
APPLY same transform to test input clusters
SPEECH "each {color} shape maps to its output partner"

@spatial_rule template_stamp
DETECT a template region (small, repeated pattern)
DETECT marker positions (dots, specific colors)
LEARN template is stamped at each marker position
VERIFY stamping matches output for all pairs
APPLY stamp template at each marker in test
SPEECH "stamp the template at each {color} marker"

@spatial_rule color_key_mapping
DETECT a color legend or key region in the input
DETECT target regions that reference the key
LEARN which key entry maps to which transformation
VERIFY key-driven transform matches output
APPLY key-driven transform to test
SPEECH "the color key tells me how to transform each region"

@spatial_rule shape_to_color
DETECT shapes in input
DETECT output has same shapes but different colors
LEARN the shape → color mapping (dots become red, lines become blue)
VERIFY mapping is consistent
APPLY shape-to-color for test
SPEECH "the shape determines the color"

the key to correspondence:
objects don't just change randomly
each input object has a PARTNER in the output
finding the partnership reveals the rule
the partnership can be:
- same color (most common)
- same position (before and after)
- same shape (structural match)
- same order (first input maps to first output)

@perceive correspondence
DETECT clusters in both input and output
MATCH clusters by color, then by position, then by shape
FOR each matched pair: what changed?
LEARN the consistent change across all pairs
